  "notes": "",
  "notes_sections": [
    "This helper multiplies the analytical FLOP count by the active weight from ``flopscope._weights`` and then applies ``int(...)`` so public estimates match budget deductions.",
    "NumPy's unwrap (``flops.lib._function_base_impl.unwrap``) does approximately 6 full-array ufunc passes: ``diff``, ``mod``, ``add``, ``subtract``, ``cumsum``, and ``where``. The ``where`` pass with two real-array arguments charges 2*(N-1) elements rather than N-1, bringing the effective total to ~7*(N-1). We charge a fixed ``7 * numel`` to approximate the sum without tracking numpy's internal implementation byte-by-byte. Issue #69."
  ],
